parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel system can cause the vehicle to stall or hesitate while accelerating, which can lead to accidents or leave the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle fails to immediately start intermittently
requiring multiple attempts to start; the vehicle hesitates while accelerating at speeds of 65 MPH and above; unknown warning lights flash on the instrument panel; the vehicle stalls.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of parts for the recall repair can cause delays and inconvenience to vehicle owners, potentially leading to continued exposure to safety risks.
symptoms: Notification of recall received
but parts are not available; dealer confirms parts are not yet available; manufacturer is aware of the issue but has not provided a solution.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake pedal can cause the vehicle to lose braking ability, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floorboard
the vehicle fails to respond to braking
the brake pedal sinks while the vehicle is in motion
loss of control of the vehicle
inability to stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended acceleration and brake failure can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially in situations where the vehicle is unable to stop or slow down in time.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates unexpectedly despite the driver's foot being off the gas pedal
the brakes fail to engage or respond slowly
the vehicle surges forward without warning
the auto brakes kick in only after the vehicle has already moved forward.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: False Activation of Automatic Emergency Braking (AEB) System
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The false activation of the AEB system can cause sudden and unexpected braking, which can lead to accidents, injuries, and even fatalities. This can also cause a loss of control of the vehicle, especially at high speeds.
symptoms: The AEB system suddenly activates without any apparent reason
causing the vehicle to brake hard
the braking system warning light flashes
the vehicle slows down or comes to a sudden stop
the driver experiences sudden jolts or jerks
and may even cause physical injury to the driver or occupants.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to disclose existing recalls and hidden defects can lead to a lack of awareness among vehicle owners, potentially causing accidents, injuries, or fatalities due to undiagnosed and unrepaired issues.
symptoms: Vehicle owners experience unexpected problems with their vehicle
which may be related to existing recalls or hidden defects. They may notice differences in vehicle performance
unusual noises
or warning lights on the dashboard.
